title: Just.Planes.Air.Tindi.Ski.Pilots
description:
Air Tindi becomes the 253rd airline to join our series and 12th airline in Canada! 
Air Tindi has been operating for more than 25 years and is now owned by Discovery Air. 
It operates more than 25 aircraft on scheduled and charter passenger and cargo flights and is the most diversified airline company North of the 60th parallel with 8 aircraft types in its fleet. 
Our program focuses on 3 of the airlines' aircraft types including the Twin Otter on skis and the rare Dash 7 and includes some fascinating flights, routes,
 destinations with what a typical winter operation looks like for the airline including Twin Otter ski landings and Dash 7 landing on a frozen lake! 

+ Cockpit filming using up to multi cameras for great views on takeoff & landing!
+ External cameras on the Twin Otter & Caravan for incredible views!!!
+ Cockpit Presentation of the Dash 7
+ Company Presentation and Flight Operations/Dispatch presentation
+ Incredible views and scenery of the area in winter
+ Flights into very remote towns, mines, camps 
+ Dash 7 landing and operation to a frozen lake
 
272 minutes
